    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-heading mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-12">
      <details class="group border border-border rounded-xl">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-heading text-sm flex justify-between items-center">
          Does Google Business Profile affect ChatGPT?
          <span class="text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Yes. ChatGPT cross-references multiple data sources including Google when answering local business queries. A complete GBP increases the consistency of your entity data across the web, which makes ChatGPT more confident in mentioning your business by name.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group border border-border rounded-xl">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-heading text-sm flex justify-between items-center">
          How many Google Reviews do I need for AI visibility?
          <span class="text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">20+ reviews puts you in a strong position. But recency matters more than volume. 10 recent reviews outperform 50 reviews from 2022. Aim for a steady flow of two to three reviews per month rather than chasing a high total number.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group border border-border rounded-xl">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-heading text-sm flex justify-between items-center">
          Should I use keywords in my GBP description?
          <span class="text-accent transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">+</span>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Yes, naturally. Include your service type, location and specialisms. Avoid keyword stuffing. Write for a human reader who also happens to be an AI. Your description should read well out loud while still containing the key terms that AI models need to categorise your business.</div>
      </details>
      <details class="group border border-border rounded-xl">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 cursor-pointer font-semibold text-heading text-sm flex justify-between items-center">
          Do Google Posts help AI visibility?
